Spatz, or should it be Spaz??  You totally dishonor a truly honorable profession. I was a Navy Corpsman, Independent Duty trained... and spent 13 years with the Marines as a Doc and am also a Viet Nam Viet.  14 ribbons and medals beginningwith the Purple Heart from Khe Sahn in Tet 1968. I imagine you'd want an award for burning your fingers while burning your draft card... Awwwww... poor baby!! Did I kill any babies? Not that I know of... but I sure as hell waxed a few adults who were trying to wax my butt. And ya know what? I don't lose a bit of sleep over it.  I took my paycheck and went where they told me to. As my friend (and I do know him in real life) says, WE are the ones who fought while you turned yellow and ran.  WE are the ones who bought you the right to voice your foul opinions and slander good men. You are scum, Spatz... nothing more, and if you want to come from behind the monitor, please send me your info, and we'll meet somewhere and discuss this. I always enjoy giving trash an &quot;Attitude Adjustment Party&quot;... Gee... do I sound upset? A bit... Your apology is as hollow as Jane &lt;spit&gt; Fonda's was. <br>
Well, to quote what you said to Paul Lavelle, an honorable man who fought for his country while you ran... FUCK YOU!!<br>
(My apologies to any ladies who may read this)<br><br>
Addison &quot;Tex&quot; Miller, HMC(FMF),USN (Ret) 
